-- Indian shares rise to record; state-run banks extend rally on new Basel deadline 
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Mar 28, 2014 06:06AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, March 28 (Reuters) - Indian shares rose to record highs for a fifth straight session on Friday as state-run lenders including State Bank of India <SBI.NS> extended recent gains after RBI extended the deadline for banks to implement Basel III rules by a year.

The NSE index <.NSEI> rose as much as 0.91 percent to an all-time high of 6,702.6, while the benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> gained 0.67 percent to a lifetime high of 22,363.97. State Bank of India Ltd <SBI.NS> provisionally rose 3.9 percent while Bank of Baroda Ltd <BOB.NS> gained 6.4 percent.